This paper discusses a method for combining lower-level models to achieve greater predictive accuracy, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically addresses issues related to classification tasks, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions comparing the performance of stacked generalization with other methods such as arcing and bagging, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS) applications. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
